cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new structural biases to the model, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates on several language pairs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories also deal with multi-lingual and image-based tasks respectively.
